issue.title: Lack of lint/code-validation
issue.body:
> Zencoder leverages a specialized proprietary AI pipeline for code generation, ensuring that the generated code is usable from the start. This proprietary AI pipeline achieves industry-leading compilation rates, making the development process more efficient.

nice. But zencoder makes again and again errors that can be catched with a simple lint.

## Expected

* At minimum, allow the agent to execute validation commands internally.
* Ideally, allow the user to configure a validation command (e.g. build, special validation sequence etc.)

## Competition

in cursor/copilot, i configured the agent to execute `npm run validate` prior to announcing/applying the results. The agent fixes the errors (cursor does this even without user confirmation).

Cursor has a build in lint, elegantly integrated with the chat panel:

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c048ee3f-b150-4688-8aa1-a3caec16d98a)

## Status

The Coding Agent still fails to execute a validate command.

The `/unittests` (Unit Test Agent) now manages to execute a custom validation command

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b90597e1-59f9-4c0a-9641-4482fd62abdc)

issue.title: Error Running Computer .../rom/apis/textutils.lua:12: attempt to call local

labels.name: bug
labels.description: A problem or unexpected behaviour with the mod.

labels.name: area-CraftOS
labels.description: This affects CraftOS, or any other Lua portions of the mod.

issue.body:
### Minecraft Version

1.20.1

### Version

1.115.1

### Details

Running the command `wget run https://phoenix.madefor.cc/try.lua` to try Phoenix or `wget run https://phoenix.madefor.cc/install.lua` to install it results in the same error:

```
Error Running Computer .../rom/apis/textutils.lua:12: attempt to call local
ComputerCraft may be installed incorrectly
```

I'm not sure how ComputerCraft could be installed incorrectly as all that's done is placing it in the mod folder.

I think this is a CC: Tweaked bug due to the error being located in textutils.

Attached are the logs:

[latest.log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20151529/latest.log)

[launcher_log.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20151532/launcher_log.txt)

[2025-05-11-1.log.gz](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20151546/2025-05-11-1.log.gz)

v2.4.0

  • Tidy up examples slightly by @​jeffwidman in dependabot/fetch-metadata#611

  • Add workflow to publish new version of immutable action on every release by @​jeffwidman in dependabot/fetch-metadata#623
  • Bump actions/create-github-app-token from 2.0.2 to 2.0.6 by @​dependabot in dependabot/fetch-metadata#621
